## 🚨 Critical Issues (Severity: BLOCKERS)

### 1. [index.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/index.js) is a 2,333-line God File
**File:** [index.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/index.js)

This is the single most critical problem. The entire backend API—**~50 route handlers** across auth, profiles, leaderboard, admin stats, GitHub OAuth, badges, peer discovery, skill gap, resume parsing, privacy compliance, and badge management—lives in **one file**.

| Concern | Lines | What's mixed in |
|---------|-------|-----------------|
| Imports (scattered!) | 1-19, 598-627, 772, 1085, 1198, 1246, 1345, 1430, 1737, 1883 | `require()` calls spread across 10+ locations |
| NLP heuristic logic | 50-202 | 150+ lines of text analysis **inline** in the entry point |
| Auth routes | 214-320 | Register, login, password reset |
| Profile routes | 349-596 | `/me`, avatar upload, public profile |
| Resume routes | 630-769 | Upload, complete, ATS result |
| Leaderboard | 776-936 | Public + admin leaderboard |
| Admin stats | 939-1033 | Departments, years, CSV export |
| Onboarding | 1048-1079 | Onboarding flow |
| GitHub OAuth | 1081-1732 | OAuth, connect, disconnect, sync |
| Skill gap | 1374-1468 | Skill analysis + peer comparison |
| Resume parsing | 1470-1544 | ATS proxy service |
| Admin intelligence | 1746-2010 | Analytics, cohorts, trends |
| Privacy compliance | 2012-2099 | Erasure, consent, export |
| Badge management | 2101-2306 | CRUD + assignment |

> [!CAUTION]
> A single syntax error, runtime exception, or memory leak in any of these 50 routes will crash the **entire application**. There is zero fault isolation.

### 2. Duplicate Route Definitions
Two routes are defined **twice**, which in Express means only the first definition handles requests — the second is silently ignored:

| Route | First definition | Second definition |
|-------|-----------------|-------------------|
| `GET /me` | Line 349 | Line 1036 |
| `GET /admin/analytics/platform` | Line 1880 | Line 1997 |

This is a **runtime bug** — the second `/me` handler (which includes `onboardingRequired` logic) is **dead code**.

### 3. No Route/Controller Separation
The backend has **zero** route files. Compare to the `ats-service` Python project which correctly uses `app/routes/`, `app/services/`, `app/models/`, `app/utils/`. The backend has middleware and models separated, but **all business logic and routes are welded together in one file**.

### 4. Security: Unauthenticated Password Reset
**Line 280:** `POST /auth/reset-password` allows **anyone** to reset **any user's password** by knowing their email. There is:
- No email verification
- No rate limiting on this endpoint specifically
- No old-password confirmation
- Only a comment saying "WARNING: This is a temporary endpoint" — but it's deployed

> [!CAUTION]
> This is a **P0 security vulnerability**. Any attacker can take over any account.

