### 7. No Environment Configuration Template
- [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/.gitignore) excludes `.env` but references `!.env.example` — yet **no `.env.example` file exists**
- New developers have no idea what environment variables are needed
- From the code, at least these env vars are required: `MONGODB_URI`, `JWT_SECRET`, `ADMIN_EMAILS`, `UNIVERSITY_DOMAIN`, `ATS_SERVICE_URL`, `AWS_*` credentials, `GITHUB_CLIENT_ID`, `GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET`, `PORT`

### 8. Stray Root-Level Python File
[sbert_service.py](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/sbert_service.py) (127 lines) sits at the project root. It's a standalone FastAPI service that should be:
- Inside `ats-service/` or its own directory
- Not dumped at the project root alongside [README.md](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/README.md)

### 9. No API Versioning
All routes are un-versioned (`/auth/login`, `/leaderboard`, `/admin/users`). Any breaking change will affect all clients simultaneously. Should be `/api/v1/...`.

### 10. Inline `require()` Calls Inside Route Handlers
Multiple route handlers do `require()` inside the function body:

```
Line 547:  const Score = require('./models/score.model')
Line 552:  const Badge = require('./models/badge.model')
Line 556:  const GitHub = require('./models/github.model')
Line 1085: const state = require('crypto').randomBytes(16).toString('hex')
Line 1180: const { BADGE_DEFINITIONS } = require('./badges')
Line 1198: const mongoose = require('mongoose')
Line 1246: const Score = require('./models/score.model')
Line 1345: await require('./badges').awardBadge(...)
Line 1430: await require('./badges').awardBadge(...)
Line 1737: const { getBadgeProgress } = require('./badges')
Line 1883: const Score = require('./models/score.model')
Line 1884: const GitHub = require('./models/github.model')
```

This is messy and makes dependencies impossible to trace. Node caches `require()` calls, so it's not a performance issue per se — but it's a **maintainability disaster**.

