## 🟡 Medium Issues

### 11. No Docker / Containerization
- No `Dockerfile` for any service
- No `docker-compose.yml`
- Three separate services (backend, frontend, ats-service + SBERT service) with no orchestration
- The SBERT service runs on port 8001, ATS on 8000, backend on 4000 — all hardcoded

### 12. No CI/CD Configuration
- No GitHub Actions workflows
- No build/test/deploy pipelines
- No linting enforcement on backend

### 13. [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/.gitignore) Has Duplicate Entries
Lines 1-4 and 6-8 both define `node_modules/` patterns redundantly.

### 14. No Input Validation Layer
- No express-validator, joi, zod, or any schema validation
- Raw `req.body` / `req.query` values used directly
- Only manual checks like `if (!email || !password)` scattered across handlers

### 15. No Centralized Error Handling
- Each route has its own `try/catch` with `console.error` + generic `500` response
- No error middleware (`app.use((err, req, res, next) => ...)`)
- No structured error codes or error classes

### 16. No Request Logging / Observability
- No morgan, pino, winston, or any structured logger
- Only scattered `console.log` / `console.error` statements
- No request ID tracking
- No correlation between errors and requests

### 17. CORS Wide Open
```js
app.use(cors())  // Line 23 — accepts ALL origins
```
Should be restricted to frontend origin(s) in production.

### 18. No Graceful Shutdown
- No `process.on('SIGTERM')` handler
- No database connection cleanup
- No in-flight request draining

### 19. Frontend [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/frontend/src/index.css) is 841 lines
A single CSS file defining the entire design system. Not using CSS modules, CSS-in-JS, or even splitting by component. All utility classes, animations, and component styles are in one blob.

### 20. No Frontend API Layer / Service Abstraction
Components likely make `fetch()` calls directly (based on pattern in similar projects). No centralized `api.js` or service layer for:
- Base URL configuration
- Auth token injection
- Error handling
- Response normalization

