## ✅ What's Done Right

1. **ATS Service Architecture** — `ats-service/` follows proper Python project structure (routes, services, models, utils)
2. **Mongoose Models** — Properly separated into individual files with consistent naming
3. **Middleware Separation** — Auth, consent, onboarding, rate limiting are properly extracted
4. **Design System** — [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/frontend/src/index.css) has a well-thought-out token system and component classes
5. **Service Extraction** — [scoreService.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/scoreService.js), [badges.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/badges.js), [analyticsCache.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/analyticsCache.js), [privacyService.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/GDGoist-ATS-Leaderboard/backend/src/privacyService.js) show intent to modularize
6. **GDPR Awareness** — Has privacy service, consent tracking, audit logging, right-to-erasure

